
[1]thief

   THIEF, n. plu. thieves.

   1. One who secretly, unlawfully and feloniously takes the goods or
   personal property of another. The thief takes the property of another
   privately; the robber by open force.

   2. One who takes the property of another wrongfully, either secretly or
   by violence. Job.30.

   3. One who seduces by false doctrine. John 10.

   4. One who makes it his business to cheat and defraud; as a den of
   thieves. Matt. 21.

   5. An excrescence in the snuff of a candle.
